## ğŸ”’ Security & Privacy Architecture

### Local-First Design Philosophy

The Butler operates on a **zero-trust, local-first architecture**:

```
YOUR MACHINE (Complete Control)
â”œâ”€â”€ Local Task Files (Encrypted)
â”œâ”€â”€ Communication Patterns (Private)
â”œâ”€â”€ Meeting Notes (Encrypted)
â”œâ”€â”€ Contact Database (Local)
â””â”€â”€ Deep Memory (Backed up to Notion only on your command)

â¬‡ï¸ [Only Explicit Data Push] â¬‡ï¸

NOTION (Backup Only)
â”œâ”€â”€ Critical task backups
â”œâ”€â”€ Notion database syncs
â””â”€â”€ [Nothing stored without your approval]

â¬‡ï¸ [Minimal, Masked Data] â¬‡ï¸

GMAIL/CALENDAR APIs
â””â”€â”€ [Read-only access, no storage]
```

### Security Features

âœ… **Local Storage** â€” All sensitive data stays on your machine  
âœ… **Encrypted Files** â€” Task notes encrypted at rest  
âœ… **API Tokens** â€” Stored securely, never logged  
âœ… **Notion Sync Control** â€” You decide what syncs and when  
âœ… **No Cloud Dependency** â€” Works offline, syncs when ready  
âœ… **Audit Logs** â€” Complete record of all operations  
âœ… **Data Portability** â€” Export all data anytime  

### Privacy Controls

```
/settings â†’ Privacy
â”Œâ”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”
â”‚ â˜‘ï¸ Auto-sync to Notion      â”‚ (Toggle on/off)
â”‚ â˜‘ï¸ Log interactions         â”‚ (Keep audit trail)
â”‚ â˜‘ï¸ Email auto-triage        â”‚ (Turn off for manual)
â”‚ â˜‘ï¸ Calendar analysis        â”‚ (Privacy mode available)
â”‚ â˜ Share insights with team  â”‚ (Disabled by default)
â”‚ â˜‘ï¸ Enable debug logging      â”‚
â””â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”˜
